AB  - In this paper we show how rational expectations models of speculative attacks on fixed exchange rate systems can be extended to take into account the possibility that the central bank could be forced to either devalue or revalue. Essential to the analysis are the concepts of buying attack and selling attack, by means of which we were able to describe how expectations about the future exchange rate are formed. We also provide a discussion on the problem of uniqueness of the equilibrium that may arise in this kind of speculative attack models.
