AB  - This paper develops a simple two-country portfolio model of the exchange-rate risk premium which incorporates price uncertainty in both countries. It is shown how the risk premium depends on the world shares of outside assets and wealth, as well as on the variance-covariance matrix of prices and the exchange rate. In particular, when purchasing power parity holds, the distribution of world wealth has no effect on equilibrium asset prices.
